You are building Phase 15 of the Yuni dating app. Read CLAUDE.md for full project context. Phases 0-14 are complete.

Build the mobile app's group date flow: group reveal, chat, post-date feedback, and match reveal.

## 1. mobile/src/api/chat.ts

- `getChatRooms()` — GET /api/chat/rooms
- `getChatMessages(roomId, limit?, before?)` — GET /api/chat/rooms/{roomId}/messages
- `getGroupDetail(groupId)` — GET /api/groups/{groupId}
- `getIcebreakers(groupId)` — GET /api/groups/{groupId}/icebreakers
- `getVenueSuggestions(groupId)` — GET /api/groups/{groupId}/venues

## 2. mobile/src/api/feedback.ts

- `submitFeedback(groupId, data)` — POST /api/groups/{groupId}/feedback
- `getMyFeedback(groupId)` — GET /api/groups/{groupId}/feedback/mine

## 3. mobile/src/hooks/useChat.ts

WebSocket hook for real-time chat:
```typescript
function useChat(roomId: string, token: string) {
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState<ChatMessage[]>([])
  const [isConnected, setIsConnected] = useState(false)
  const wsRef = useRef<WebSocket | null>(null)

  // Connect to ws://host/api/ws/chat/{roomId}?token={token}
  // On message: parse JSON, add to messages
  // On close: set isConnected=false, attempt reconnect after 3s
  // sendMessage(content): send JSON {type: "message", content}
  // sendTyping(): send JSON {type: "typing"}
  // cleanup on unmount

  return { messages, isConnected, sendMessage, sendTyping, loadHistory }
}
```

`loadHistory`: calls getChatMessages REST endpoint for older messages (pagination).

## 4. Screens

### mobile/src/screens/GroupRevealScreen.tsx
- Header: activity name + date/time
- Member cards: show each member's photo, name, age, program. Use a horizontal scroll or grid layout.
- Venue suggestions section: list of suggested venues with name, address, price range
- Icebreaker section: show 3 icebreaker prompts
- "Open Group Chat" button → navigates to ChatScreen with the group's chat room ID
- Status indicator: "Upcoming" / "Today!" / "Completed"

### mobile/src/screens/ChatScreen.tsx
- Message list (FlatList, inverted for newest-at-bottom)
- Each message: sender name, content, timestamp. Different style for own messages vs others.
- Text input + send button at bottom
- Typing indicator ("Sarah is typing...")
- Load older messages on scroll to top (pagination)
- Works for both group chat and 1-on-1 chat (same component, different room ID)

### mobile/src/screens/PostDateScreen.tsx
- Shown after a group date is completed (navigate from group detail or push notification)
- **Experience Rating**: 1-5 stars (tap to rate)
- **Romantic Interest**: for each other member in the group, show their photo + name with a heart button (yes/no toggle). Default: not selected.
- **Block**: small "block" button next to each member. Confirmation dialog: "Block this person? You won't be matched with them again."
- **Report**: "Report a member" button at bottom. Opens a modal with member picker + category picker (uncomfortable, inappropriate, misrepresentation, aggressive) + optional description.
- **Submit** button: sends all feedback at once.
- After submission: show "Thanks for your feedback!" If there are mutual matches, show a celebration screen and navigate to MatchRevealScreen.

### mobile/src/screens/MatchRevealScreen.tsx
- Celebration animation or design (can be simple for MVP — just a header "It's a match!")
- Shows the matched partner's photo, name, and bio
- "Send a message" button → navigates to ChatScreen with the 1-on-1 chat room ID
- "Back to Home" button

## 5. Update Navigation

- GroupRevealScreen accessible from HomeScreen (tap on upcoming group)
- ChatScreen accessible from: GroupRevealScreen (group chat), MatchRevealScreen (1-on-1), Chat tab (list of all rooms)
- PostDateScreen accessible from GroupRevealScreen when group status is "completed"
- MatchRevealScreen shown after submitting feedback if mutual matches found
- Chat tab: show list of chat rooms (ChatRoomsScreen) → tap opens ChatScreen

### mobile/src/screens/ChatRoomsScreen.tsx
- List of all chat rooms the user is in
- Group chats: show group activity + member names
- Direct chats: show partner's name + photo
- Last message preview + timestamp
- Navigate to ChatScreen on tap

## 6. Tests

### mobile/__tests__/hooks/useChat.test.ts
- Mock WebSocket. Verify connection URL includes room ID and token.
- Verify sendMessage sends correct JSON format.
- Verify received message is added to messages state.

### mobile/__tests__/screens/ChatScreen.test.tsx
- Renders message list and input field
- Renders send button

### mobile/__tests__/screens/PostDateScreen.test.tsx
- Renders star rating
- Renders interest toggles for each member
- Renders submit button

IMPORTANT:
- ChatScreen must work for BOTH group chat and 1-on-1 chat — same component, different room ID
- The WebSocket URL uses the token as a query parameter (not header)
- Post-date feedback must include an entry for every other member (interested: true/false)
- TypeScript must compile clean
